       </article>
       <a href="https://wikiedu.org/blog/2018/07/18/an-assignment-that-inspires-students-beyond-the-classroom/">
       </a>
       <h2 class="side">
        <a alt="Link to full article" href="https://wikiedu.org/blog/2018/07/18/an-assignment-that-inspires-students-beyond-the-classroom/">
         An assignment that inspires students beyond the classroom
        </a>
       </h2>
       <article>
        <img alt="An assignment that inspires students beyond the classroom" class="right" src="_images/news/one-off/158px-University_of_California,_San_Diego_seal.svg.png"/>
        <p class="p1">
         It’s rare that students return to a research paper or project after their work has been graded, and even more rare after their course has ended. That’s the power of a Wikipedia assignment. As instructors and students have recounted, when students learn how to evaluate and contribute to Wikipedia as an assignment, inspiration can reach beyond the classroom.
        </p>
       </article>
       <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/07/06/sports/world-cup/russia-yashin-starostin.html?rref=collection/sectioncollection/sports&amp;action=click&amp;contentCollection=sports&amp;region=rank&amp;module=package&amp;version=highlights&amp;contentPlacement=4&amp;pgtype=sectionfront">
       </a>
       <h2 class="side">
        <a alt="Link to full article" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/07/06/sports/world-cup/russia-yashin-starostin.html?rref=collection/sectioncollection/sports&amp;action=click&amp;contentCollection=sports&amp;region=rank&amp;module=package&amp;version=highlights&amp;contentPlacement=4&amp;pgtype=sectionfront">
